cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.CY 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a technique for generating artificial datasets using generative adversarial networks (GANs) and evaluates the quality of the generated data by training machine learning models on it. It also involves the use of a Gaussian noise layer in the discriminator to ensure differential privacy, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper involves the generation of synthetic data, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.DB (Databases). The use of GANs also suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves the generation of privacy-preserving data, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.CY (Computers and Society).
